data.content:
## .NET 10 OpenAPI Breaking Changes

The root cause is **Microsoft.OpenApi upgraded from v1.x to v2.x**, which targets OpenAPI 3.1. Here are the specific breaks and fixes:

### 1. `OpenApiString` / `IOpenApiAny` removed
The entire `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` namespace is gone. Use `System.Text.Json.Nodes` instead:

```csharp
// Before
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// After
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

Map: `OpenApiString` → `JsonValue.Create(string)`, `OpenApiInteger` → `JsonValue.Create(int)`, `OpenApiArray` → `JsonArray`, `OpenApiObject` → `JsonObject`.

### 2. `Schema.Nullable` removed
OpenAPI 3.1 uses type unions instead of a `nullable` flag. `OpenApiSchema.Type` is now a `JsonSchemaType` flags enum:

```csharp
// Before
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// After — remove the null flag from the type
property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;

// (To make something nullable, you'd do:)
// property.Value.Type |= JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

### 3. `ReferenceType` → string-based `ReferenceType`
`ReferenceType` values are now string constants rather than an enum:

```csharp
// Before
new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }

// After
new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
// This one still compiles, but note ReferenceType is no longer an enum —
// it's a static class with string constants. No code change needed here
// unless you were doing enum-specific operations (switch, cast, etc.).
```

### 4. `OpenApiSecurityRequirement` dictionary change
`OpenApiSecurityRequirement` no longer inherits from `Dictionary<OpenApiSecurityScheme, IList<string>>`. Use its `Schemes` property:

```csharp
// Before
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
};

// After
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { Schemes = { [oAuthScheme] = scopes } }
};
```

### Fixed code (complete)

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
    {
        Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
    };
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { Schemes = { [oAuthScheme] = scopes } }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

**Summary of namespace changes:**
| Remove | Add |
|---|---|
| `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;` | `using System.Text.Json.Nodes;` |
